4.73/5  rDev +1.7%look: 4.5 | smell: 4 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5Enjoyed from a can. 
Color: N/A
Aroma: pine 10/10
Mouthfeel: oily, 2/10 carbonation
As a west coast hop aficionado, I heard of heady topper, the beast of the east. I waited several years to try this beer. Expecting an aggressive hop bomb, I was disappointed at first; but then the rolling resin hit. Fresh pine off the bat followed by grapefruit smoldering into delicious resin that lingers. The linger is gratuitous, nicely piney and bitter. The malt is excellent but coated richly by hop aroma, whether it is a complement or burried is lost to me. May you decide. 569 charactersBbless, May 26, 2017
