3.91/5  rDev -15.9%look: 4 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 3.75 | feel: 4 |  overall: 3.751 PINT can
Served in a tulip glass, directions be damned
This beer pours like pineapple juice and is topped with two inches of fluffy beige head that leaves little lacing on the glass.
In the aroma I get orange, grapefruit and pine.
The taste is all grapefruit and pine. The bitterness builds the more I drink.
Medium mouthfeel
The smell indicated a juicy IPA, while the flavor was quite bitter. This is the third time I have gotten the opportunity to try this beer, and it was the first full can that I consumed. I cannot say that it lives up to the hype. I'll take Hop Juju all day, everyday over this. Some day when I make it to Vermont, I will have some guaranteed fresh and see if that changes my mind. I have no idea how old this can is. It was given to me by a friend over the weekend. I can't believe it's more than 2 or 3 weeks old, but I could be wrong. 868 charactersbuschbeer, Mar 07, 2017
