4.99/5  rDev +7.3%look: 4.75 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5Appearance: Very light and cloudy. Straw colored murky beer with particles floating around.
Aroma: Citrus fruits, primarily grapefruit and orange juice. Tropical elements are certainly here along with fresh pine / hop scents. Very very enjoyable and pleasing smell to this. Not really any bready malts to speak of.
Taste: It's been a little over a month since my last can so this description will not do the brew justice. I remember it being magical yet very confusing. An extremely delicate, soft and gentle beer on the palate but the amazing flavors still awaken all of the taste buds. The finish is a thing of beauty, the bitterness and tropical hop flavors linger and make your mouth water. The aftertaste is the most striking characteristic of this beer, it's hard to think of a beer that makes your palate beg for the next sip so aggressively. Dangerous beer. Doesn't drink like an 8 percenter.
Mouthfeel: soft, velvety, medium-ish body. Creamy hop juice. 
Overall: This is one the best IPA's I have ever consumed. Hope to have it fresher or even on tap some day. 1,073 charactersluisitoelmatador88, Mar 06, 2016
