4.46/5  rDev -4.1%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Beer review number 1000. Lucked out getting this. Sometimes the stars align...drank half from the can and poured half into a snifter.
Poured a gorgeous pale cloudy color with a super fluffy tight bubbled head that lasts forever. Reminds me of a Belgium beer.
Smell is similar to a saison. Spicy hops, light sweet malt, lemon, orange and pineapple.
Taste is big hops at the front of the tongue, semi-sweet malt in the middle and a dry bitter finish. The malts become more prominent and sweeter as it warms. I get a slight pepper taste as the hop bitterness builds after each swallow. Quite unique for the style. Hides the 8% ABV really well.
Very smooth and easy to put down. Everything works well here. 
A very well crafted brew. Tasty and approachable. It is worthy of the hype? Maybe, maybe not. In a world of diverse hop profiles and a ton of awesome DIPAs that are readily available, it certainly fits in with the best of them. Stocked that I got my hands on one. 972 charactersChrisMon02, Feb 27, 2016
