4.38/5  rDev -5.8%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.5Exceptional double IPA.  No debate, no discussion.  This is not a review which argues that this beer is over hyped.  I think Alchemist are doing it the way it should be done.  Make an excellent product, sell it locally and don't expand.  
It wasn't the best beer I've ever had.  It was an excellent scent-laden IPA.  It has wonderful art and a great drink.  I doubt I'm the only person to pound this beer in the parking lot of a random Vermont corner store.  It got me very drunk, and exceptionally jolly.  I bought it and had to determine if I needed to buy more to ship home.   (There were several cases available fresh from the delivery).
After the first sip, I knew that I just wanted to drink these 4 beers on vacation and not stress it.  Fighting the collector impulse is hard sometimes, but this is a better experience than a notch-on-the-belt beer.  I drank one heady topper in the parking lot, one while watching Bernie kick everyone's ass in the debate (Vermont pride), and one while meandering around a foliage view.    I left the fourth beer unfinished.  
I'm glad that Heady Topper is in the world.  I'm glad I got to try it.  I think it is worth consuming this beer with love and respect.   Thanks Alchemist. 1,225 characterskingmaxwell, Oct 20, 2015
