4.25/5  rDev -8.6%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 3.5 |  overall: 4.25Broke the rules and poured it out of the can into a chalice. This beer was canned three weeks ago.
L- Golden-orange and hazy. Thick white creamy head that is very well-retained.
S- Resinous and citrusy American hop aroma dominates. Some fruity esters (peach, stone fruit) present as well. Malt is subdued - slightly biscuit-like.
T- A crisp, juicy flavor that balances hop and yeast character very well. Not excessively bitter, but hop bitterness is present (especially in the finish).
F- Fairly dry throughout with a harsh dry, bitter finish.
O- I wish I could try this beer fresh from the brewery. A very good IPA that is slightly hindered by a harsh finish. 665 charactersaobrehm, Sep 11, 2015
