4.54/5  rDev -2.4%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.5Purchased 4-pk of 16oz cans at bottle shop in Winooski, VT  in mid-October 2014...delivered that day from the brewery. 
Drank chilled in the can (as instructed...!?), so there are no comments on the pour, the color, the clarity, the head. or lacing.      
Sniffing at the can top (like some kind of rummy), the aroma is very citrusy and pungent...good start.. 
Taste doesn't disappoint.  Well....it wouldn't if not for all the hype.  "The best IPA in the world" ?!  Who's smoking the crack?  
I've had several west coast IPAs and DIPs that are at least as good as -- some better -- than this.  It is nice to have a high-quality beer brewed in the untouched purity of Vermont...I get it...but let's not lose our minds. 
A very good beer.  I liked it, and I'd buy more.  But I probably won't drive a full day specifically to buy it....again. 840 charactersbilbobrewer, Aug 14, 2015
