4.88/5  rDev +4.9%look: 4 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5Thanks Adam for the can!
No date, but the smell and flavor seems right on, so....here's the rest.
Yeah, I poured a little bit out into a mini snifter, I had to, I wanted to see it, so sue me.
The appearance was a hazy pale orange color with a thin whimsical white foamy head. Lacing is few and far between, but I see the floaties, hmmmm....unfiltered, right? Okay, I get it, I think.
The smell started off with pure lovely grapefruit rind. Light grassy to citrusy tones amplify a really nice smooth aroma (I'm guessing because this is unfiltered, right?)
The taste rides a pure eloquent bittersweet bliss of the grapefruit. It runs the gamut on my taste buds. A slight bitter citrus rind aftertaste rides into the finish really awesome.
The mouthfeel starts with a sweet crisp refreshing feel sliding into the bittersweet grapefruit rind-like substance pummeling my tongue really nicely. Carbonation is right on par.
Overall, holy shit, this stuff is spectacular. So glad a buddy sent this to me! 996 charactersSitkaSteve, Aug 03, 2015
