4.86/5  rDev +4.5%look: 4.75 | smell: 5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 5Hadn't had Heady in about year and a half. Since then I have tried a plethora of new amazing beers from up and coming breweries, like TreeHouse and Trillium, which made me wonder if I still liked Heady just as much as I used to. I was able to score a can last week and had it yesterday for my birthday. To my surprise, it still lives up to its hype! It might not be my favorite DIPA anymore, but it is definitely up there in the top 5.
Drank half from a snifter, the second half from the can.
L: golden straw in color; hazy but not muddy; can see some light coming through it. 
S: Dank goodness. a lot more herbaceous and resinous than what I remember, some citrus, some biscuity malt and a slight hint of  tropical fruits, but very minimal. 
T: Follows. More citrus notes and a decent amount of lingering bitterness. 
M: Nice and pillowy, on the medium to full side. Wonderfully frizzy carbonation
O: Just excellent. As I said, top 5 DIPA for me. 953 charactersdiemilio, May 26, 2015
