4.59/5  rDev -1.3%look: 4 | smell: 3.75 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 4.75A friend from Vermont hooked it up and brought a few cans over.
Appearance:  I drank it from the can (as instructed), so I'm not sure. The can is interesting enough.
Aroma:  Possibly muted due to the can. I was expecting something more intense, but it has a nice piney-hop aroma.
Taste:  I took one sip and was overwhelmed by waves of pine and citrus long after swallowing. 
Mouthfeel: A bit on the syrupy side, but has an incredibly smooth and clean finish.
Overall:  I won't hesitate to call it the best IPA/DIPA I've tried.  I had a Sculpin immediately afterwards and it paled in comparison. 599 charactersshillzor, Mar 27, 2015
