4.49/5  rDev -3.4%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.5Pours a hazy bright orange with a thick soapy white head. The smell hits with a floral quality but you will get some tropical fruit notes if you really dig your nose in; pineapple, mango, melon, a bit of juicey orange, and a touch of sweetness. That sweetness comes through even more on the taste, almost honey or brown sugar-like, not really your typical malt sweetness. There is some mild fruitiness again, I'd say the best descriptor is ripe cantaloupe but there is some melon, guava, and papaya in there as well. Mouthfeel is soft and sticky, not too much bitterness, the sweetness lingers. Definitely hides the 8% ABV well.
I can see why many say this is the best beer in the world, it's very approachable and very smooth. My favourites in the style tend to be a little more brazen and bold but this is certainly a great beer. 832 charactersBeervana, Mar 19, 2015
