4.39/5  rDev -5.6%look: 4 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.5My 600th Beer Advocate review. Enjoyed on my birthday 02/21/15.
I poured about 2 ounces of this into a glass in order to rate it's appearance. The remaining beer was left in the can as requested by the brewer's notes.
This poured slightly more pale yellow than I expected, with a 1/2 inch white head that left strands of lace. 
The smell is of citrus fruit, tropical fruit and faint pine. 
The taste is bitter grapefruit, subtle tropical fruit sweetness followed by pine bitterness on the finish. 
The texture is medium bodied with medium carbonation. 
This is a very well balanced double IPA. Not a one-dimensional hop bomb by any means. World class without a doubt. 673 charactersFurlinator, Feb 22, 2015
