4.86/5  rDev +4.5%look: 4 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 5Okay, I've had a bunch of Heady since my initial review here. Since that one was less than 150 characters, let's do one tonight that counts. Can is roughly 2 weeks old. Thanks, Theresa! :)
Look: I've poured it into a glass before when sharing it, it looks okay. I generally drink it from the can. Can't ignore those capitol letters, right?
Smell: Mmmm! Floral, piney, citrusy, and that deliciously tropical Conan yeast. Even though this beer is rather different from Lawson's Sip of Sunshine, they're definitely brewed with the same, very estery yeast.
Taste: Yes! 100% deserving of the hype. I feel like I've been largely desensitized to bitterness with all these IPAs, but Heady definitely brings the IBUs here in a noticeable way. It's not to the extreme, but the bitterness pleasantly intermingles with the dank floral, piney, fruity hops; it's super drinkable, I have to repeatedly tell myself to slow down because, not only is this an 8% beer, it's a rare treat. Left to my own devices, I could definitely guzzle a can or two in a very short amount of time.
Feel: Fluffy with perfect carbonation. The only reason it's not a 5 is because I've had Double Citra by Hill Farmstead. That's what a perfect mouthfeel is like. That said, this is pretty close.
Overall: 1000% worthy of the hype, don't listen to anyone who says otherwise. Go on, make a pilgrimage to Waterbury. Heck, stay at the Stagecoach Inn, eat at Hen of the Woods, and make a weekend out of it. You won't be disappointed. 1,495 charactersOnemoresolo, Feb 06, 2015
