4.59/5  rDev -1.3%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75Appearance: pours a light honey color. a small half-finger to finger of a foamy white head with good retention and a solid lacing. completely hazy and opaque.
Smell: strong hoppy bouquet, notes of honeydew and other melons, papaya, orange, pine and bold hop resin. light lemon bread malt sweetness in the background. 
Taste: opens up with a flavorful but not over the top hop taste. first comes the fruits, mainly tropical but including orange, honeydew, cantaloupe. after the fruit it develops some pine taste. the malt backbone is barely there, giving a light lemon bread sweetness. Right at the end a strong bite of hop resin comes through.
Mouthfeel: medium bodied. bitterness is bold but not overly assertive and doesn't linger too long. slight dryness that adds to the refreshing qualities. strong drinkability.
Overall: needless to say a top notch beer. I don't think its my favorite DIPA but that isn't because it isn't a superbly crafted beer. And don't forget to drink it from the can. the taste is better than from a glass. 1,038 charactersSportsandJorts, Jan 13, 2015
