4.96/5  rDev +6.7%look: 4.75 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 5Worth the hype? Oh yeah! This is probably the best smelling and best tasting beer in its class I have ever had. 
Appearance: I drank two. 1 I poured into a glass (Which is not recommended and the second one I drank from the can as instructed to give it the full evaluation). Cloudy yellow not much red in this one but a bit. Decent amount of head that settled pretty quickly. 
Aroma: Holy hell this has the best nose of any IPA I have ever had! The only thing close is probably Sculpin. Earthy dankness some sandlewood notes, floral and some citrus fruits rind in there as well. Its amazing how much they put into the bouquet of this beer.
Taste: Here you go, this is the best IPA in the world, perfectly balanced IPA, not too bitter not too malty just perfect balance. Piney resinous hops dominate, but you also detect some citrus notes in there as well. I think this is just another perfect example of NE IPA's, its earthy. That is what we get from these, they are not bitter bombs like West Coast style IPA's but they are a category all of their own. This one I would describe as floral citrus fruit forward and a lot of dank earthiness going on as well.
Overall: Amazing experience. I wanted to end the old year with a bang and begin the second half of my journey after Pliny with something amazing, and I have! Thoroughly enjoyable beer and I would drink it as often as I could get it! 1,394 charactershumuloner22, Jan 01, 2015
