4.53/5  rDev -2.6%look: 4 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Type: 16-oz. can
Glass: Firestone pint glass
From: My friend Chad
Price: ??
Purchased: ??
Consumed: Nov. 19, 2014
Misc.: N/A
Thanks Chad!
Poured a honey, orange, hazy color with two fingers of off-white, frothy head. Sporadic foamy lacing on the sides of the glass. Great retention on the top all the way down. (Sight - 4.00)
Smelled potent juicy hops from the get go. Got Citra hops, tropical hops, juicy peaches, tangerine, nectarine, Ruby Red grapefruit , orange, floral hops, pine, mango juice, caramel, passion fruit, slight pineapple juice and faint wet Cascade hops. Pretty damn good on the nose. (Smell - 4.75)
Taste wasn’t quite as good as the nose, but still pretty great. Got tropical hops, passion fruit, grapefruit juice, mango, pineapple juice, Citra hops, nectarine, peaches, tangerine, caramel and astringent bitter finish. Felt like I could taste pulp it was so thick. A bit boozy late. (Taste - 4.50)
Medium body. Creamy texture. Average-to-lively carbonation. Abrupt, fruity, refreshing finish, but bitterness lasts for some time on the tongue after. (Feel - 4.50)
So glad I got a chance to try this one. One of the best IIPA’s I’ve had. (Overall  - 4.50)
