4.88/5  rDev +4.9%look: 4.25 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75Pint can poured into a pint glass (because I wanted to look at it). No date that I can see -- but purchased a week ago today, and flown home in a friend's luggage. Another gift from him that elicited a nerdy gasp of delight when I found it on my desk.
Pours hazy golden with a perfect inch of surprisingly coarse head that stays standing for some time, and relaxes more than fades. Smell is excellent, beautiful bright floral and citrus notes with a strong pine note, clean fresh hop aroma (I'm not sure I've ever smelled a beer that smelled this similar to actual living hops).
Taste is so hop forward. Delightfully so. Resin, intensified grapefruit rind, pine, just enough honeysuckle and tangerine sweetness to balance. Bitter finish is ridiculously long.
Mouthfeel is thick and filmy, but the film is delicious. Overall, unsurprisingly, this is on my short list of best beers I've ever tasted. I would love to do a side by side comparison with some of the others. 970 characterssnaotheus, Oct 16, 2014
