4.96/5  rDev +6.7%look: 4.75 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 5I really am not a fan of this new "ratings" system. However if the only way for my rating to count is to review, so be it. This is what the gold standard should be for a DIPA.  Magnificent in every way.
A: well... its in a can, and while i may look like superman.. i sadly do not have x Ray vision... however i have poured this in a glass and personally i love the unfiltered hazy orange yellow look. Lets me know its about to go down.
S:  Blast to the nostrils. Fruits, peach and orange and nectarine. Pine also and extremely floral. amazing Nose on this.
T:  Perfection at what it is. Balanced with that malty sweet frutiness, bitter finish.
F: amazing coating, not too carbonated to give you a creamy feel, and the flavor lingers well after it its gone.
O: There is a reason this is one of the best. Even with all the new young studs this still holds it down.  Is this the best DIPA ive ever had, no. But it surely is one of them and worthy of such high praise. 
Side note: I now reside in California and get fresh Pliny whenever i want and it cannot hold a candle to Heady IMO. I can get bored of Pliny, and im always "Ready for a Heady" 1,141 charactersHop_God, Oct 13, 2014
