5/5  rDev +7.5%To be fair, my buddy and I drove up to VT to get our hands on this beer that is in high demand and only sold in VT.
Appearance:  Would not know as we drank them in the can.
Aroma:   Citrus fruits, mint, hops.
Taste:   Wow.   This beer is a wonderful balance of fruit and massive hops.   It starts off with the citrus fruits that are in the nose, and then the name of the beer comes into play as the hops just do not stop.  I would say it is a bit on the dry side in the finish.
Overall:  AMAZING!!   The can says it all, "so drinkable it is dangerous."   My only knock on this beer is the availability.   I understand the buzz that is created with the elusive factor of beers like this, Pliny, Founder's KBS, etc.   And while the brewer John Kimmich has every right to keep this limited, I would suggest he brew more and make it available to more states (just a business take IMO).   Nevertheless, we ended up getting four cases between four people and have enjoyed this all summer down here in New Jersey, and will be back in VT next summer to get more (or sooner if we ski).   And while we had other great IPA's in Vermont such as Lawson's and Hill Farm Stand, this one (to me) is just so drinkable it is scary in a good way.  Cheers!! 1,238 charactersdahlen22, Aug 26, 2014
