4.88/5  rDev +4.9%look: 4.25 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75A: The website made me categorize this even though it tells you to drink from the can. The can's art is kinda nice...
S: Amazing, as many others have said. Lots of fresh hop smell with a nice citrus aroma.
T: Fantastic. With the IBU's coming in at 75, it's neither too overwhelming nor boring. Well bittered for the style. Grapefruit and sticky resin notes.
M: Smooth and appropriately bitter on the tongue. Not overly carbonated.
O: Living in VT and being able to get this all the time (at least Thursday afternoons) where I live I may be biased, but Heady Topper is one of the best DIPA's I've had. At 8% ABV it's biting but not overwhelming (I do like a high ABV stout or barleywine) and keeps it crisp with the aroma hops addition(s). Delicious and perfect for a VT summer BBQ. 785 characterslifenoob, Jun 20, 2014
