5/5  rDev +7.5%JDoogle, May 30, 2014
4.99/5  rDev +7.3%look: 4.75 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5I was lucky enough to visit the cannery before it was closed to the public and have been able to get a few cans of Heady from various friends since then. Every time I have one, it's a borderline religious experience.
A: Orange-yellow, hazy, with a good chance of a few floaters. The appearance wasn't a turn off for me, but I can see how it would be for some people, hence the very slight deduction in this category. If you only have one can of Heady, do yourself a favor and follow the recommendation of drinking straight from it. It does make a difference.
S: Pine, loads of citrus, weed, moss. Dank. The first whiff when you open the can is hard to describe but it's amazing. 
T: Huge hop bomb, but what's scary is that it doesn't have any of the bitterness that a lot of DIPAs out there have. It's ridiculously smooth and drinkable. You can literally distinguish every note of this beer, whether it's the citrus, pine, weed/moss- there isn't one note that overpowers the next. And you can pick out something different in every sip. Simply amazing.
M: This is another category that I think really sets Heady apart from other DIPAs, including Pliny. I personally prefer the silkier and thicker unfiltered mouthfeel of Heady. Others may not have this preference, but I think the added body really adds to the whole experience. 
O: Heady Topper is the real deal. I can honestly say it is the best beer I have ever had. I'm always a little sad when I'm finishing my last can because I know it'll be a while before I'll be able to get another. I just wish the Alchemist would start distributing in Boston... 1,610 charactersVTbrewfan, May 30, 2014
