4.97/5  rDev +6.9%look: 4.5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5Drank straight from the can, but I poured a small amount in to a snifter to rate the appearance even though I feel like it is tough to rate on that since the brewer clearly wants it to be drank from the can.
A - it pours a great orange amber with a small head. Lots of particulate in suspension, yeast and hop resin. Again the beer doesn't look bad, but I feel it is tough to rate because of how the brewer intended it to be consumed.
S - This beer smells fantastic. Hops, orange, pine, lemon, citrus, I even get some mint. So many complex scents coming from this beer it is amazing. I want to bury my nose in the can and get high off the fumes.
T/M - This beer taste even better than it smells. All of the scents come through in the flavor. Notes of orange, piney-citrus, and mint roll across the tongue so smoothly. And of course there is the hops. The hopping is done so well in this beer you get the giant hop flavor with out giant hop bitterness. This is the first and only beer I have ever had that has pulled this off. There is so much hop flavor, but the bitterness you experience isn't overwhelming at all. The hops flavor comes in waves of slight bitterness that build as you roll the beer through your mouth. I am just bewildered as to how they accomplished this amazing and delightful experience. 
