4.62/5  rDev -0.6%look: 4.5 | smell: 5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5A fresh can into a standard pint glass.
Hazy golden yellow with orange highlights, some floating sediment can be seen and a decent amount of lazy bubbles that raise to the top. A thin white head rests at the top and some lacing happens as the beer is drank down.
Pine with mango and pineapple greet your nose, then move into grapefruit like citric qualities. A soft graham cracker like sweetness layered below that, with a fresh cut grass and peach aroma. Pretty awesome smelling, and unoffensive even though it has that pine resin in the forefront which I typically do not care for. 
Opens with more pine resin, then moves into pineapple sweetness with grapefruit zest to compliment. Softer notes of graham cracker, mango, and that nice peachy sweetness. Great stuff.
Crisp, medium bodied with a bit of stickiness and a touch of drying.
Awesome representation of pine resin with notes of grapefruit and pineapple, with a softer graham cracker like sweetness. A top 10 beer right now that lives up to the hype in my opinion. Glad they have made this one more accessible. 1,075 charactersauroracrisis, Nov 26, 2011
