A: Beer pours a hazy golden/orange with minimal head.
S: Smells absolutely incredible. Hops and pineapple make my mouth water. 
T: Similar to the smell, but a little pinier and not quite as citrusy/sweet as I expected. It's damn hoppy, but not overwhelmingly bitter, and has a pretty tame low-key malt presence. A sticky hops flavor lingers.
